        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 11 at 12:58AM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 1255 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of slow-moving
thunderstorms with very heavy rain along a line extending from near
Hoffman to 7 miles southwest of Rockingham. Movement was northeast
at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Minor flooding.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...One to two inches of rain will result in ponding of water
and a risk of minor flooding.

Locations impacted include...
Hamlet, Laurel Hill, Aberdeen, Pinebluff, Laurinburg, Foxfire,
Ellerbe, Southern Pines, East Rockingham, and Rockingham.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall may lead to localized flooding. Do not drive
your vehicle through flooded roadways.</instruction>
